Please note that since `SDL_Point` and `SDL_FPoint` are distinct types with different member types (`int` for `SDL_Point` and `float` for `SDL_FPoint`), we can overload the `DistanceSquared` function for each type without templates.

In your `Circle` class methods, you can use `DistanceSquared` by passing the `SDL_Point` or `SDL_FPoint` members accordingly.

For instance, within `Circle::ContainsPoint` and `Circle::IntersectsCircle`, you would call:

```cpp
// For Circle with SDL_Point
bool ContainsPoint(const SDL_Point &point) const {
    return DistanceSquared(center.point, point) <= (radius * radius);
}

// For FCircle with SDL_FPoint
bool ContainsPoint(const SDL_FPoint &point) const {
    return DistanceSquared(center.point, point) <= (radius * radius);
